REASONING: According to the CIA World Factbook ranking of real GDP per capita (PPP) for 2024, Singapore ranks #1 with $132,600, followed by Luxembourg at #2 with $128,200 and Monaco at #3 with $115,700

The Wikipedia page on nominal GDP per capita shows Monaco at the top with $256,581 (2023), followed by Liechtenstein with $207,973 (2023), and Luxembourg with $140,941 (2025 IMF estimate), while Singapore is not listed in the top positions shown
There appears to be a difference between nominal GDP per capita and real GDP per capita (PPP) rankings - Singapore leads in the PPP-adjusted measure which accounts for cost of living differences

The CIA World Factbook data is more recent (2024 estimates) compared to some other sources and uses purchasing power parity adjustments which provide a more accurate comparison of living standards across countries
